headline: $9.8 Billion Utilities ETF Is A 3% Yielding Backdoor Bet on AI’s Explosive Growth
summary: The Vanguard Utilities Index Fund ETF Shares (NYSEARCA:VPU) generates its 2.73% dividend yield by holding a diversified portfolio of 67 utility companies across the electric, gas, and water sectors. Investors receive quarterly distributions funded by the dividends these underlying holdings pay out.
